abstract: >-
  An original research programme investigating whether number theory - and
  possibly mathematics more broadly - emerges as the erasure-shadow of a
  quantity-free foundational information system (the Genesis Information System),
  posited behind an epistemic barrier that is unfalsifiable by construction. The
  central bridge is the Resistance Isomorphism, the logarithm Omega(1/n) = ln n,
  read as the Landauer erasure cost of an integer, which unifies number theory,
  Boolean logic, circuit topology, and information theory as one algebraic
  structure. The programme develops the formal consequences of the posit under a
  strict explore-then-criticise discipline, grading every claim as Fact, Reading,
  or Lead. Originating theory and axioms are Alexander Pisani's; formalisation,
  connective mathematics, and computation were developed jointly with Claude
  (Anthropic). No claim is made on the Riemann Hypothesis.
keywords:
